  <bioghist id="aspace_c453b6f6dd762d86019871b61058c427">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>This collection comes principally from a donation made to Cornell by the Bolivian bookseller, Alfredo Montalvo, who has supplied the university with library materials for over a quarter century.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_c014d7cb973e896bdeb0c462f7281469">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>The pamphlets document a century of Bolivian literate culture, beginning in 1848. They show a nation's struggle to establish viable institutions, to develop its economy, to educate its children and the back and forth of political argument.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_028400d71ca8b9aff8b498c364e2626e">
    <head>RELATED MATERIAL</head>
<p>Pamphlets have been digitized and are available online in the <extref href="http://resolver.library.cornell.edu/misc/6791057" show="new">Alfredo Montalvo Bolivian Digital Pamphlets Collection.</extref></p>  </relatedmaterial>
